@dev Calculates the total depth of base tokens available for a given maximum price.
The function steps through each price level until the maximum price is reached,
accumulating the depth available at each price level.
NOTE: This function uses a while loop which could potentially run out of gas if the
maximum price is set too high compared to the current price. Users should ensure that
the maximum price is set to a reasonable level relative to the current price before calling
this function.
@param baseToken The base token that the user is interested in.
@param quoteToken The quote token that would be used to buy the base token.
@return depth The total depth of base tokens available at the current price

@notice Executes a token swap following a specified path of pools.
@dev The function determines the best price for the desired output and swaps tokens accordingly.
If the user specifies a desired output greater than what's available at the current best price,
they'll receive the maximum possible at that best price.
If the desired output is less than the available amount at the best price, they'll receive the exact amount they desire.
@param path The array of tokens representing the swap path.
@param desiredAmountOut The desired amount of the final token in the path to receive.
@param maxPrice The maximum acceptable price for the entire path, scaled by PRECISION.
@param recipient The address to receive the swapped tokens.
@param deadline The time by which the swap should be completed.
@return actualAmountOut The actual output amount of tokens received.
@return amountInUsed The actual input amount of tokens used.
